This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it deals with neural network compression techniques for image classification tasks. The use of Bayesian optimization also suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper's focus on quantization and pruning techniques aligns with the neural networks (cs.NE) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories.
